text: Ambivali Tarf Tungaratan is a census town in Raigad district in the state of Maharashtra, India. ==Demographics== India census, Ambivali Tarf Tungaratan had a population of 6796. Males constitute 55% of the population and females 45%. Ambivali Tarf Tungaratan has an average literacy rate of 73%, higher than the national average of 59.5%; with 59% of the males and 41% of females literate. 15% of the population is under 6 years of age. ==References== Category:Cities and towns in Raigad district
